comment:
* Implement a stack of simple integers.
 *
 * %OPT%
 * This is currently based on IntVector, which permits fast acess but pays a
 * heavy recopying penalty if/when its size is increased. If we expect deep
 * stacks, we should consider a version based on ChunkedIntVector.
 * @xsl.usage internal

methods.name: public int push(int i)
methods.comment: * Pushes an item onto the top of this stack. * * @param i the int to be pushed onto this stack. * @return the item argument.

methods.name: public final int pop()
methods.comment:
* Removes the object at the top of this stack and returns that
   * object as the value of this function.
   *
   * @return     The object at the top of this stack.

methods.name: public final int peek()
methods.comment:
* Looks at the object at the top of this stack without removing it
   * from the stack.
   *
   * @return     the object at the top of this stack.
   * @throws  EmptyStackException  if this stack is empty.

methods.name: public int peek(int n)
methods.comment:
* Looks at the object at the position the stack counting down n items.
   *
   * @param n The number of items down, indexed from zero.
   * @return     the object at n items down.
   * @throws  EmptyStackException  if this stack is empty.

methods.name: public void setTop(int val)
methods.comment:
* Sets an object at a the top of the statck
   *
   *
   * @param val object to set at the top
   * @throws  EmptyStackException  if this stack is empty.

methods.name: public boolean empty()
methods.comment: * Tests if this stack is empty. * * @return true if this stack is empty; * false otherwise. * @since JDK1.0

methods.name: public int search(int o)
methods.comment: * Returns where an object is on this stack. * * @param o the desired object. * @return the distance from the top of the stack where the object is] * located; the return value -1 indicates that the * object is not on the stack. * @since JDK1.0

methods.name: public Object clone() throws CloneNotSupportedException
methods.comment:
* Returns clone of current IntStack
   * 
   * @return clone of current IntStack
